{
  "article_id": "HutchingsCaliforniaMagazine1857",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "Our readers will remember that in the November number of the Magazine we were favored by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. C. J. W. Russell",
        "entity_key": "cru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", with the narrative of "
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who was eighteen years alone, on the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Island of San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Since the publication of that sketch, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. R.",
        "entity_key": "cru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "has paid a visit to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. George Nedever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the gentleman who discovered her, was presented with a water-bottle made of grass, and a stone mortar, necklace and other things that were made by her during her long and solitary residence. The water-bottle explains its own use. The mortar was used for pounding the aulone, the Haliotis of naturalists, and which was one of the principal articles of food among "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and by whom they were dried for winter use, and afterwards pounded in a mortar before eating."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "At the present time there are no less than twelve schooners and sloops chartered by Chinamen; besides several hundred of Chinese laborers engaged in this business, as they are an important article of consumption to Chinamen in "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in addition to the vast quantities exported by them to "
      },
      {
        "text": "their native land",
        "entity_key": "co_china",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". In flavor these are said to be fully equal to the oyster, especially in soup, and could be introduced advantageously for our own use, and we would suggest to epicures here, to give this dish of \"John's\" a trial, for it may be possible that although we might not relish cooked rats, the aulone may be one of the greatest of delicacies to our own people."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "(The aulone is the fish taken from the pearl oyster.)"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The necklace made by "
      },
      {
        "text": "this ingenious woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was of slate, and although rude, it was prized by her as a great ornament, even though no one was near to admire or praise her."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "There is upon "
      },
      {
        "text": "this island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "a good sized cave in which she took up "
      },
      {
        "text": "her abode",
        "entity_key": "re_lwcave",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and on the walls of which she had kept a rude record of all the vessels that had passed "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and of all the most remarkable occurrences in her lonely history, such as seeing large quantities of seals, hailing of vessels in the distance, &c."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "By her signs she represented herself as once being very sick, and had to crawl upon her hands and knees from the cave to some water. During her sickness at ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nedever's",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "nideverhouse",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", although she suffered much, she never complained, and made them understand that she should like to die, for then she should meet ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in the spirit land.",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "We append the following interesting extract from the Santa Barbara Gazette."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\""
      },
      {
        "text": "All that was known of ",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          4,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this remarkable woman",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          4,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and all of her history while living upon ",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          4,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this island",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          4,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she was able to impart by signs and gestures, (she had lost the knowledge of language), and the manner of her discovery and deliverance, her arrival here and death that soon followed, has before been published. While living she was an object of lively interest to some and curiosity to others",
        "tropes": [
          10,
          4,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"Speaking with a friend lately, an old and respectable resident of "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", on this and kindred topics, we were enabled to trace the history of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "inhabiting "
      },
      {
        "text": "this",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "other islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in "
      },
      {
        "text": "our channel",
        "entity_key": "re_sbchannel",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "back to the year 1811. The account given of the war of extermination* against "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "on "
      },
      {
        "text": "this particular island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is not uninteresting, and runs thus:"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"In the year 1811, "
      },
      {
        "text": "a ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_charon",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "† owned by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Boardman & Pope",
        "entity_key": "bp",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Boston",
        "entity_key": "ci_bo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", commanded by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. Whittemore",
        "entity_key": "whi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", trading on "
      },
      {
        "text": "this coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", took from the port of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Sitka, Russian America",
        "entity_key": "ci_si",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", about thirty "
      },
      {
        "text": "Kodiak Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a part of "
      },
      {
        "text": "a hardy tribe",
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "inhabiting the "
      },
      {
        "text": "island of Kodiak",
        "entity_key": "i_ko",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Channel",
        "entity_key": "re_sbchannel",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", for the purpose of killing sea otter, which were then very numerous in the neighborhood of "
      },
      {
        "text": "these islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. Whittemore",
        "entity_key": "whi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", after landing "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Kodiaks",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and placing in their hands fire-arms and the necessary implements of the chase, sailed away to the coast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Lower California",
        "entity_key": "re_baja",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and "
      },
      {
        "text": "South America",
        "entity_key": "re_southamerica",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\""
      },
      {
        "text": "In the absence of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_charon",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a dispute arose between ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Kodiaks",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands [sic]",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", originating in the seizure of ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the females",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "by ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Kodiaks",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The Kodiaks",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "possessing more activity, endurance and knowledge of war, and possessing superior weapons, slaughtered ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the males",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "without mercy, old and young. On the ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "island of San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", not a male, old or young, was spared.",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "At the end of a year "
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. Whittemore",
        "entity_key": "whi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "returned to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands [sic]",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", took "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Kodiaks",
        "entity_key": "natam_kodiak",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "on board, and carried them back to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Sitka",
        "entity_key": "ci_si",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"From this period little is known of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "remaining on "
      },
      {
        "text": "these islands [sic]",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "till the year 1836, when "
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. Isaac Williams",
        "entity_key": "iwi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", late Collector of the Port of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", visited "
      },
      {
        "text": "this island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in "
      },
      {
        "text": "a small vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and took on board all the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "remaining but "
      },
      {
        "text": "one woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who was left in the manner stated by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. Russell",
        "entity_key": "cru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in the California Magazine. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "were of the type of the coast Indians, and were no doubt a part of them.\""
      }
    ]
  ]
}